{"word":"coriolis effect","results":[{"definition":"(physics) an effect whereby a body moving in a rotating frame of reference experiences the Coriolis force acting perpendicular to the direction of motion and to the axis of rotation; on Earth the Coriolis effect deflects moving bodies to the right in the northern hemisphere and to the left in the southern hemisphere","partOfSpeech":"noun","inCategory":["natural philosophy","physics"],"typeOf":["event","issue","outcome","result","consequence","upshot","effect"]}]}